===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|académie}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|acadēmīa}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|Ἀκαδημία}}, a grove of trees and gymnasium outside of Athens where [[w:Plato|Plato]] taught; from the name of the supposed former owner of that estate, the [[w:Attica|Attic]] hero [[w:Akademos|Akademos]]. Compare [[academe]], [[academia]], [[Akademeia]].

